Sarkozy Rejects Criticism, Says Ireland Is Exiting Crisis

-- B y   M a r k   D e e n
-- 
2011-10-23T14:59:47Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-23/sarkozy-rejects-criticism-says-ireland-is-exiting-crisis.html
French President  Nicolas Sarkozy 
rejected suggestions that European leaders have failed in their
efforts to stem the financial crisis. He said Ireland is exiting
the danger zone and that without action by France and  Italy , the
economic situation would have been worse. He spoke to reporters
in Brussels today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Mark Deen in Paris at 
 markdeen@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
